                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/></desc></decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#146r" facs="148"/><desc>Portrait of the owner Ǝğğǝgu Nǝguśe and his wife, Zäwditu, and other family members,  with caption (top to bottom): <q> “How Ato Ǝğğǝgu and Wäyzäro Zäwditu prayed and said, ‘the things of this world are temporary and may He prepare the heavenly place,’” “Aräfu,” “Fäläqäč,” “Ada Ayäläč,”  “how Wäyzäro Zäwditu pleaded by the name of Mary."</q></desc></decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#146v" facs="149"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> with <persName ref="PRS3827Ephrem"/>, with caption <q>“How Ephrem, [the Syrian,] has praised our Lady Mary.”</q></desc></decoNote>
                        <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d7">
